  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6 and boil a kettle</p><p>Rinse your <strong>sushi rice </strong>in a sieve under <strong>cold running water</strong> for 30 secs (use your hands to really wash the grains!), then set aside to drain fully</p><p>Add the <strong>sushi rice </strong>to<strong> </strong>an <strong>oven-proof dish </strong>with 250ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [375ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[500ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong>, cover tightly with<strong> tin foil </strong>and put the dish in the oven for 25 min or until all the water is absorbed and the rice is cooked</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1663834127037-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1663834127037-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1663834127037-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1663834127037-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1663834127037-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once cooked, transfer the <strong>cooked</strong> <strong>rice</strong> to a plate and set aside for 10 min or until the rice is cooled</p><p>Meanwhile, cut your <strong>cucumber</strong> in half lengthways and scrape out the inner seeds with a teaspoon, throw the watery seeds away, then slice finely and add to a small bowl with your <strong>rice vinegar </strong>and a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Stir everything together and set aside – this is your<strong> quick-pickled cucumber</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1663834131520-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1663834131520-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1663834131520-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1663834131520-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1663834131520-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and grate (don't chop!) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Combine <strong>half</strong> your <strong>soy sauce </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) and the<strong> grated garlic </strong>(not a big fan of raw garlic? Try using less!) in a bowl with your <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong> – this is your <strong>dipping sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1663834135939-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1663834135939-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1663834135939-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1663834135939-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1663834135939-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>basa fillet[s]</strong> into large, bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped basa</strong> to a large bowl with the <strong>remaining soy sauce</strong>, then set aside to marinate</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1663834140117-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1663834140117-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1663834140117-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1663834140117-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1663834140117-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>sriracha</strong> (not a fan of spice? Just add a little!) and <strong>mayo</strong> in a small bowl – this is your <strong>sriracha mayo</strong></p><p>Rinse your<strong> blanched edamame beans</strong> under <strong>cold running water</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>rinsed edamame beans</strong> to a bowl with <strong>half</strong> of the <strong>sriracha mayo</strong> (you’ll use the rest later!) and a good grind of <strong>black pepper </strong>and give everything a good mix up – this is your<strong> edamame salad</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1663834145009-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1663834145009-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1663834145009-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1663834145009-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1663834145009-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a very generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable</strong> <strong>oil</strong> (enough to coat the base of the pan) over a medium-high heat</p><p>Add your <strong>cornflour</strong> to the <strong>marinated basa </strong>and give everything a good mix up until the basa is fully coated</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>coated basa</strong> and cook for 4-5 min on each side or until cooked through – this is your <strong>crispy soy basa</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1663834149213-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1663834149213-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1663834149213-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1663834149213-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1663834149213-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the rice is cooled, roll into 3 balls per person – these are your <strong>sushi rice balls</strong></p><p>Tip: Use wet hands to make it easier!</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1663834153044-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1663834153044-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1663834153044-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1663834153044-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1663834153044-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>crispy soy basa</strong> with the <strong>sushi rice balls</strong>, <strong>edamame salad</strong> and <strong>quick-pickled cucumber </strong>(reserve the pickling liquid) to the side</p><p>Drizzle the<strong> remaining sriracha mayo</strong> over the rice balls and sprinkle over your <strong>shichimi togarashi </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!)</p><p>Combine the<strong> reserved</strong> <strong>pickling liquid</strong> and the <strong>dipping sauce </strong>and serve it to the side and enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
